# Sequoia v{{.Version}} — AI Code Audit System

Sequoia is installed and provides comprehensive multi-agent code auditing.

## Agent Roster

| Agent | Role | Trigger |
|-------|------|---------|
| C0 Orchestrator | Coordinates all agents and synthesizes findings | All /sequoia commands |
| C1 Context | Builds the Project Map (stack detection, size estimation) | /sequoia init, always first |
| P1 Security | Authentication, injection, secrets, attack surface | Always |
| P2 Performance | Bundle size, queries, caching, Core Web Vitals | Frontend, backend, fullstack |
| P3 Architecture | Patterns, coupling, API design, tech debt | Always |
| P4 Quality | Test coverage, naming, dead code, documentation | Always |
| P5 Experience | Accessibility, UX patterns, conversion flows | Frontend, fullstack, mobile |
| P6 Operations | CI/CD, containerization, observability, IaC | Backend, fullstack, infra |
| P7 i18n | I18n, locale, RTL, translation keys | All /sequoia commands |
| M1 Correlator | Deduplicates and correlates findings across agents | After all phase agents |
| M2 Reporter | Calculates Health Score, generates deliverables | Final step |

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/sequoia init` | Initialize Sequoia. Builds Project Map. Always run first. |
| `/sequoia audit` | Full audit — all agents, correlation, Health Score 0–100. |
| `/sequoia review` | PR/diff review — faster, focused on changed files. |
| `/sequoia fix` | Generate actionable tasks from latest audit findings. |
| `/sequoia diff` | Compare current state against last recorded audit. |

## Health Score

`score = 100 − Σ(severity_weight × scope_multiplier)`
- critical=15, high=8, medium=4, low=2, info=0
- scope_multiplier: 1.0 (isolated) | 1.5 (shared root cause)

## Quick Start

Run `/sequoia init` first, then `/sequoia audit` for a full analysis.
